cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The authors also derive theoretical statistics for patch-wise differences, which suggests information theory (cs.IT) may be relevant. Additionally, the use of probabilistic weights and similarity measures could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI).
